---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Privacy Policy | Manopause"
  description="How we protect your privacy and handle your information. Your safety and privacy are our top priorities."
>
  <main class="legal-page">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="page-header">
        <span class="category-label">Legal</span>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: December 2024</p>
      </header>

      <div class="content">
        
        <section class="highlight-box">
          <h2>The Short Version</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>We don't track you personally</li>
            <li>We don't sell your data to anyone</li>
            <li>We don't require accounts or personal information</li>
            <li>We use minimal analytics (if any) to improve the site</li>
            <li>Your safety is more important than our metrics</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Why Privacy Matters Here</h2>
          <p>
            We understand that people visiting this site may be in sensitive or 
            even dangerous situations. Someone monitoring your internet activity 
            could use your visit here against you. That's why we've designed this 
            site with your privacy and safety as top priorities.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Information We Don't Collect</h2>
          <p>We do NOT collect:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Your name, email address, or other personal identifiers</li>
            <li>Information that could identify you as an individual</li>
            <li>Any account information (we don't have accounts)</li>
            <li>Data about your specific situation or circumstances</li>
            <li>Location data beyond general region (country/state)</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Information We May Collect</h2>
          <p>
            Like most websites, our hosting service may automatically log some 
            technical information:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Basic analytics:</strong> Page views, general geographic 
              region, device type (mobile/desktop), and browser type. This helps 
              us understand if people can access our content.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Server logs:</strong> IP addresses may be temporarily logged 
              by our hosting provider (GitHub Pages) as part of standard web 
              infrastructure. We do not access or analyze these logs.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We use this information only to understand how to improve the site 
            and ensure it works properly across different devices and browsers.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Cookies</h2>
          <p>
            This site uses minimal to no cookies. We do not use:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Advertising or tracking cookies</li>
            <li>Third-party analytics that track you across websites</li>
            <li>Social media tracking pixels</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            If we use any analytics in the future, we will choose privacy-respecting 
            options and update this policy accordingly.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
          <p>
            Our site is hosted on <strong>GitHub Pages</strong>, which is operated 
            by GitHub (owned by Microsoft). Their privacy practices are governed by 
            their own privacy policy:
            <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-privacy-statement" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              GitHub Privacy Statement
            </a>
          </p>
          <p>
            When we link to external resources (hotlines, other organizations), 
            those sites have their own privacy policies. We cannot control how 
            they handle your information.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Your Browser History</h2>
          <div class="safety-note">
            <h3>⚠️ Important Safety Information</h3>
            <p>
              While we don't track you, <strong>your browser does</strong>. If 
              someone has access to your device, they may be able to see that 
              you visited this site through:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Browser history</li>
              <li>Recently visited sites</li>
              <li>Autofill suggestions</li>
              <li>Downloaded files</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              If you're concerned about someone monitoring your activity, consider:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Using private/incognito browsing mode</li>
              <li>Clearing your browser history after visiting</li>
              <li>Accessing from a library computer or trusted friend's device</li>
              <li>Visiting our <a href="/tools/digital-safety">Digital Safety</a> page for more guidance</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
          <p>We will NEVER:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Sell your data to anyone</li>
            <li>Share your information with advertisers</li>
            <li>Provide your information to third parties for marketing</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We may share aggregated, non-identifying information (like "10,000 people 
            visited last month") in impact reports or grant applications, but this 
            information cannot be used to identify any individual.
          </p>
          <p>
            The only exception to our no-sharing policy would be if we were legally 
            compelled to share information (such as by a valid court order). However, 
            since we don't collect personal information, we would have very little 
            to share.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            We provide educational content that may be accessed by children and teens. 
            We do not knowingly collect any personal information from anyone, including 
            children under 13. Our site does not have accounts, forms, or other ways 
            to submit personal information.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p>
            If we make significant changes to how we handle privacy, we will update 
            this policy and the "Last updated" date at the top of this page. We 
            encourage you to review this policy periodically.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Contact</h2>
          <p>
            If you have questions about this privacy policy, you can reach us at:
            <strong>privacy@manopause.info</strong>
          </p>
          <p class="note">
            (Note: This email may not be active during our early development phase.)
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="related-links">
          <h2>Related</h2>
          <div class="link-list">
            <a href="/terms">Terms of Use</a>
            <a href="/accessibility">Accessibility</a>
            <a href="/about/ethics">Our Ethics</a>
          </div>
        </section>

      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    --primary: #2563eb;
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 1rem 4rem;
  }

  .page-header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
  }

  .category-label {
    display: inline-block;
    background: #eff6ff;
    color: var(--primary);
    padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    color: #1e293b;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .last-updated {
    color: #64748b;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .content section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .content h2 {
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    color: #1e293b;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .content p {
    color: #475569;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .content ul {
    color: #475569;
    line-height: 1.8;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .content li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .content a {
    color: var(--primary);
  }

  .content a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .highlight-box {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #ecfdf5 0%, #d1fae5 100%);
    border: 1px solid #a7f3d0;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
  }

  .highlight-box h2 {
    color: #065f46;
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .highlight-box ul {
    color: #047857;
    margin: 0;
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .highlight-box li {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .highlight-box li::before {
    content: '✓';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: #059669;
  }

  .safety-note {
    background: #fffbeb;
    border: 1px solid #fcd34d;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }

  .safety-note h3 {
    color: #92400e;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .safety-note p, .safety-note li {
    color: #92400e;
  }

  .note {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #64748b;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .related-links {
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .related-links h2 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .link-list {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .link-list a {
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    background: #f8fafc;
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: #475569;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    transition: border-color 0.2s, color 0.2s;
  }

  .link-list a:hover {
    border-color: var(--primary);
    color: var(--primary);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .page-header h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .highlight-box {
      padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
